# Prisma v7 Rules

## Critical: Prisma v7 Breaking Changes
- `PrismaClient` is imported from `'../generated/prisma/client'` (NOT `'@prisma/client'`)
- The `datasource db` block has NO `url` property — connection is passed via the pg adapter
- Always instantiate: `new PrismaClient({ adapter: new PrismaPg({ connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL! }) })`
- Config lives in `prisma.config.ts`, NOT in `schema.prisma`
- Run `npx prisma generate` after any schema change
- Run `npx prisma migrate dev --name <name>` to create migrations

## Schema Conventions
- All models use `@id @default(dbgenerated("gen_random_uuid()")) @db.Uuid`
- Timestamps: `createdAt DateTime @default(now())`, `updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt`
- JSON fields typed as `Json` in Prisma map to `Record<string, unknown>` in TypeScript
- Enums are defined in `schema.prisma` and referenced directly

## The `db` singleton
Always import from `@/lib/db` — never instantiate PrismaClient directly in route files.
